Edition:
Quote:  KOKOPU <i>Galaxias fasciatus</i> Gray. It is often called Mountain [115] Trout but it is also found practically at sea level, just above high- tide mark, as I have often caught specimens in small creeks near the sea at Portobello, in Otago Harbour.
